          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "وَقَالَ رَجُلٌ لِأَبِي جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ إِنِّي إِمَامُ مَسْجِدِ اَلْحَيِّ فَأَرْكَعُ بِهِمْ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "أَسْمَعُ خَفَقَانَ نِعَالِهِمْ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "أَنَا رَاكِعٌ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فَقَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:57:61",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1152",
      "text": [
        " «اِصْبِرْ رُكُوعَكَ وَ مِثْلَ رُكُوعِكَ فَإِنِ اِنْقَطَعُوا وَ إِلاَّ فَانْتَصِبْ قَائِماً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1152 - A man said to Imam Abu Ja'far (as),\n\"I am the Imam of the mosque in our neighborhood, and when I bow (in ruku') with them, I hear the sound of their footsteps while I am in ruku'.\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Remain in your bowing position for as long as your bowing takes, and if they catch up, (continue); otherwise, stand up straight.\""
        ]
      }
    },
